35:39.018 --> 35:41.237
yeah? i'd give you
this assignment for a nickel.

35:43.656 --> 35:46.409
bobby and andy cleared
that street homicide, huh?

35:46.409 --> 35:48.912
that first guy they liked's
a scumbag, but it looks
like he wasn't in it.

35:49.412 --> 35:51.447
that arthur?
arthur goes in last year...

35:51.447 --> 35:55.668
for a double child homicide,
rats another con out
for killing a guard.

35:55.668 --> 35:58.454
arthur's back out
on the street.
uh-huh.

35:59.923 --> 36:02.709
how far are you into this guy?
i guess about halfway.

36:02.709 --> 36:06.262
assuming it's me into him.
i'm not sure what you mean.

36:06.262 --> 36:10.099
neither am i.
do you like him?

36:10.099 --> 36:13.553
no. he's a real bad guy.

36:13.553 --> 36:16.556
and i'm in kind of a state
off some personal stuff,

36:16.556 --> 36:20.560
so, um, it's kinda hard
to stay on top of things.

36:20.560 --> 36:23.279
all's i gotta do is remember
i'm a good girl, right?

36:23.279 --> 36:26.616
that's, uh--
that's the rumor
i've been hearing.

36:26.616 --> 36:30.737
- what do you mean?
- everyone says
  what a good cop you are.

36:30.737 --> 36:34.290
good person.
yeah, huh?

36:37.660 --> 36:39.879
- i gotta pee.
- good night.

36:39.879 --> 36:42.999
good night, diane.

37:08.440 --> 37:11.660
- this is so good.
- yes. yes.

37:17.666 --> 37:21.336
was it a really big
left turn for you?
finding out i was gay?

37:21.336 --> 37:25.173
i-- i-- i won't deny
 i was somewhat surprised.

37:25.173 --> 37:28.426
well, i really hope that doesn't
stop us from being friends.

37:28.426 --> 37:32.180
you know, to be honest,
abby, i feel like...

37:32.180 --> 37:35.100
y-you could've told me earlier
in on knowing each other.

37:35.100 --> 37:36.968
you know, saved me some
awkwardness in my thinking.

37:38.470 --> 37:40.472
every time you came by...

37:40.472 --> 37:42.223
the machines,
you were like a kid...

37:42.223 --> 37:44.476
who was afraid of the water,
you know?

37:44.476 --> 37:47.312
you were sort of looking to me
for encouragement.

37:47.312 --> 37:49.531
i was worried
that if i told you...

37:49.531 --> 37:52.734
that i was gay,
it might scare you away
from exercising.

37:53.234 --> 37:55.070
oh.
and then i thought
i'd tell you,

37:55.070 --> 37:58.039
and i'd stop using the machines
for a while.

37:58.039 --> 37:59.874
but that was me
10 years ago.

37:59.874 --> 38:02.827
nah. that--
that would've been silly.

38:02.827 --> 38:06.331
i sure hope we can get over
this hurdle,

38:06.331 --> 38:09.834
'cause i think you're
a really nice person,

38:09.834 --> 38:11.670
and i enjoy
spending time with you.

38:11.670 --> 38:15.090
well, i-i do with you as well.

38:15.090 --> 38:18.593
and your story
of being concerned
over my physical well-being,

38:19.094 --> 38:20.979
well, that-- that
doesn't surprise me at all--

38:20.979 --> 38:22.981
that type consideration.

38:22.981 --> 38:25.350
i'm-- i'm sure that's
very characteristic of you.

38:25.350 --> 38:29.020
thanks, greg.
not at all.

38:31.940 --> 38:34.275
did you enjoy your meals?
very much.

38:34.275 --> 38:37.662
it was really good.
very much so.

38:48.506 --> 38:51.376
i can sign you out with me
if you'd like to come to dinner.

38:51.376 --> 38:55.880
- put my nose in it.
- no one wants to rub your nose
  into anything, maceo.

39:02.053 --> 39:04.606
[ sighs ]

39:06.608 --> 39:09.477
the future keeps telling us
what the past was about.

39:09.477 --> 39:12.480
you make the past
mean different things...

39:12.480 --> 39:16.484
by the way you use
the time that comes after.

39:19.487 --> 39:23.491
a few years ago,
you spent some time with
people who loved you, maceo.

39:23.491 --> 39:27.996
that doesn't have to be some
dream set away from
the rest of your life.

39:29.998 --> 39:34.002
lillian and the girls would be
so happy to see you again.

39:34.002 --> 39:36.004
you can meet
our little boy.

39:36.004 --> 39:38.006
what's his name?

39:38.006 --> 39:40.008
he's named after me.

39:42.510 --> 39:44.512
why don't you come home
with me, maceo?

39:44.512 --> 39:46.514
junior's got girls
on all sides of him.

39:46.514 --> 39:49.400
he'd love to have
an older boy at the table.

39:52.854 --> 39:54.856
i'm grateful
you're helping me.

39:57.275 --> 39:59.160
remember, life dealt you
this card too.

40:26.771 --> 40:29.274
[ chattering ]

40:32.110 --> 40:33.945
hee-ho.
hiya, jimmy.

40:33.945 --> 40:37.615
mmm, looks yummy.

40:37.615 --> 40:40.401
i was just
sitting here realizing
i hadn't eaten all day.

40:40.401 --> 40:42.737
timmy, when'd you make the soup?

40:42.737 --> 40:46.407
lay off my mulligatawny.
did he tell you
what day he made it?

40:49.878 --> 40:52.881
a fella called.
he'll call back at 9:00.

40:54.549 --> 40:57.585
not be in.
said he'd call.

40:57.585 --> 41:01.840
- what's his big problem?
- that's him, you know.

41:01.840 --> 41:04.642
yeah, great.

41:08.596 --> 41:11.349
i'm surprised at you, jimmy,
telling your business
in front of me.

41:16.738 --> 41:21.492
a white fella's supposed
to ride with me to meet
some... other people.

41:21.492 --> 41:26.781
be here at 9:00 for the ride.
who are the other people?

41:26.781 --> 41:28.583
i thought you said you didn't
do business with black guys.

41:31.920 --> 41:35.256
you know, mouse,
you stop drinking ginger ale,
maybe i'd confide in you more.

41:35.256 --> 41:40.461
no, jimmy.
in some ways i'd like to,
but i don't wanna start.

41:48.269 --> 41:51.306
slide that soup my way, huh?
i haven't ate all day either.

41:51.306 --> 41:53.691
sure.

41:55.193 --> 41:59.113
[ sniffing ]
mmm.

41:59.614 --> 42:02.033
how's work?
you gotta buy a building.

42:02.033 --> 42:05.403
let me fix it up.
a couple months,
that'll be doable.

42:05.403 --> 42:07.038
yeah?
what's in a couple months?

42:07.538 --> 42:10.742
but not if you're with
a boss, you know.
you step out on your own.

42:10.742 --> 42:12.961
i'm game.
 i'm not afraid.

42:12.961 --> 42:15.914
be a little afraid, mouse.
keeps you careful.

42:17.832 --> 42:21.135
mmm. mmm. mmm!

42:21.135 --> 42:27.141
timmy, it's awful.
up yours, jimmy.

42:30.929 --> 42:35.183
two months, mouse.
that's four times 576.
ak-47s.

42:35.183 --> 42:38.686
the first and 15th if those
knuckle-draggers aren't lying.

42:40.154 --> 42:41.990
like i understand
what you just said.

42:41.990 --> 42:44.943
all for the noble cause.

42:44.943 --> 42:48.246
which is what?
what?

42:48.246 --> 42:50.498
what's the noble cause?

42:50.498 --> 42:52.917
i don't know
any noble causes, mouse.

42:52.917 --> 42:56.337
i know a bunch of assholes
in belfast like singing
themselves to sleep.

42:56.838 --> 42:59.173
and maybe i get to buy
you a building, but--

42:59.173 --> 43:02.510
i don't understand what you're
saying half the time, jimmy.

43:02.510 --> 43:06.381
it's not important, is it?
what?

43:06.381 --> 43:08.683
there you go.

43:13.521 --> 43:15.940
-slide that soup back over here.
-sure.

43:21.863 --> 43:24.315
i haven't eaten all day.
yeah, you were saying.

43:24.816 --> 43:26.951
- i feel light-headed.
- you sleeping all right?

43:27.452 --> 43:30.705
oh, pretty much.
i got some situations.

43:30.705 --> 43:34.709
i got a family situation,

43:34.709 --> 43:37.495
another situation.

43:37.495 --> 43:41.249
um, anyway--

43:41.249 --> 43:44.052
those are keeping you up?

43:44.052 --> 43:50.008
um, no, not really.
you know, you just--

43:50.008 --> 43:53.144
you get upset
and so forth and--

43:56.514 --> 43:59.317
you wanna get out
of dodge, mouse?
you feeling light-headed?

43:59.317 --> 44:02.603
mmm. i feel like i said yes
to that scotch.

44:02.603 --> 44:05.857
how do you like that,
the penance without
the pleasure, huh?

44:06.357 --> 44:08.659
oh, yeah.
that's what it feels like.

44:08.659 --> 44:11.029
you wanna get outta here, mouse?

44:12.530 --> 44:15.533
um--

44:15.533 --> 44:18.336
yeah, maybe.
maybe we should go.

44:18.336 --> 44:20.705
sure. you know,
